# Project Structure

This is a monorepo with four top-level packages: `backend/`, `frontend/` (React web app), `mobile/` (Expo/React Native app), and `common/` (shared code).

## Workspace Layout

| Package | Framework | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| `backend/` | Node.js / Express | GraphQL API server |
| `frontend/` | React / Vite | Web application |
| `mobile/` | Expo / React Native | iOS & Android app |
| `common/` | TypeScript | Shared types, styles, utilities |

## Directory Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `backend/mutations/` | GraphQL mutation resolvers |
| `backend/queries/` | GraphQL query resolvers |
| `backend/helpers/` | Shared utility functions |
| `backend/db/models/` | Sequelize database models |
| `backend/test/helpers/` | Unit tests |
| `backend/test/integration/` | Integration tests |
| `frontend/src/pages/` | Route components |
| `frontend/src/components/` | Page-specific components |
| `frontend/src/core/components/` | Shared/reusable components |
| `mobile/src/screens/` | Screen components by feature |
| `mobile/src/components/` | Reusable UI and domain components |
| `mobile/src/stores/` | Zustand state management |
| `mobile/src/services/` | Apollo client, auth, storage |
| `common/schema.graphql` | GraphQL schema (generates types) |
| `common/src/` | Shared utilities (e.g., `emailHtmlStyles.ts`) |

## Shared Code (`common/`)

Code that must stay consistent between web and mobile belongs in `common/src/`. Examples:
- `emailHtmlStyles.ts` — CSS/HTML generation for email rendering (used by both `HtmlViewer` on web and `WebView` on mobile)
- `schema.graphql` — GraphQL schema (generates types for backend and frontend)

## Environment Configuration

- Access all environment variables through `backend/config/env.ts`
- Never hardcode AWS credentials or secrets
- Use `config.isProduction` and `config.isDevelopment` flags

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use logger from `backend/helpers/logger.ts` instead of `console.log`
- Follow existing patterns for GraphQL (use codegen from `common/schema.graphql`)
